@JRBobDobbs-b7n  you are a unicorn sir. I don't think I've spoken to anyone who thinks Marvel is hot garbage right now who didn't also acknowledge that you go woke you go broke. Odd, but refreshing.
As for the movie, idk something about going to the theater and watching it myself instead of listening to a reviewer changed my mind. It's probably just MCU recency bias, or the fact I don't see movies in public a lot anymore, but the movie was effective on me. At first, I didn't vibe with the humor and the undertones of depression, but by the end I was super stoked when this ragtag group pulled together and helped this poor mentally ill dude come back to reality and start to heal his hurt. It was a good ending imo. But the "New Avengers" at the end there did feel a little bit shoved in there just to drum up more interest. I guess I'm okay with that.
It's also crazy how much they're pushing Fantastic 4 in all the meta. If it's as good as this one was, I'll probably enjoy that too. It's okay to enjoy things sometimes.
